-- Germany’s Renewable Subsidies to Rise 50%, Handelsblatt Reports
-- B y   A n n e t t e   W e i s b a c h
-- 2012-06-13T19:35:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-13/germany-s-renewable-subsidies-to-rise-50-handelsblatt-reports.html
Germany’s subsidies for renewable
energy will increase more than expected in the coming years,
 Handelsblatt  reported, citing a confidential strategy paper from
the  Environment Ministry .  The subsidies will amount to 150 billion euros ($188.6
billion) by 2031 in contrast to an earlier forecast for 100
billion euros, Handelsblatt said, without disclosing how it got
the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Annette Weisbach in Frankfurt at 
 aweisbach1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at 
 fconnelly@bloomberg.net  